  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although \"Arrival Cities\" has yet to achieve significant citation metrics or online visibility, it holds strong potential for future scholarly and public engagement, evidenced by established commercial linkages with platforms like Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published by Leuven University Press in 2020, \"Arrival Cities\" enters the academic landscape with a solid foundation despite currently having no citations or direct public engagement metrics. Its presence on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads indicates a commercial linkage that suggests an interest in its content among broader audiences; this could be a pathway to enhance its visibility in scholarly discourses and beyond.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the absence of mentions on platforms like Wikipedia and Reddit limits the observation of high-fidelity social and community discourse, it does not negate the potential for future discussions around the themes presented in the book. The topic of urban studies and the experiences faced by newcomers in metropolitan environments is highly relevant, and as societal debates evolve, the work may find its resonance in ongoing conversations.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The inferred role of \"Active public discourse\" showcases a gentle yet existent acknowledgment of the themes encapsulated in \"Arrival Cities.\" Given the current context of migration and urban adaptation, there appears to be a fertile ground for the book to contribute to wider academic discussions as well as public discourse in the future.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As the field of urban studies continues to grow, \"Arrival Cities\" possesses the potential to generate interest among researchers looking for contemporary resources to cite. The lack of immediate citations should be viewed within the larger context of the gradual adoption of academic works, particularly those that engage with complex societal issues. This foundational research output is situated within a timely discourse that can gain traction as its themes become increasingly salient in addressing contemporary urban challenges.</p>",
